captions.text: [MUSIC PLAYING]
-Hi guys.
It's Brooklyn and Bailey.

And today our video is all about
some of our favorite things,

so that we can give you guys
an idea for your Christmas wish
list.
Christmas wish list.
-Christmas wish list.
There you go.

We are giving you guys ideas
for your Christmas wish list.

For our first items on the list
we asked for more eyeglasses,
because we're just that nerdy.

Actually, they are
from zennioptical.com.

They're just these really
inexpensive glasses.

-You can get them
in different shapes,

different sizes,
different colors.
-Any colors.
Yeah.

-And the prices range
from $6 to $20, $30.
-Really inexpensive.

-And it's the same price
for prescription glasses.

So you can get them
prescribed or not prescribed.
And they're all the same price.

-Obviously, we have
our prescribed,

cause we're about
as blind as bats.
So.
-Very blind.

-You want glasses for
your Christmas wish list,

just go to zennioptical.com,
and you can find them.

-Next we are going
to have jewelry.

And you can buy jewelry at
any of your favorite stores.

You can either ask
for a gift card there,

so you can go buy some jewelry
and some clothes, maybe.

Or you can just go
and buy the jewelry.
-Which I do.

-And the prices can range
from $3 to-- I don't know.
-$10, maybe.

Depending on how cool the
necklace or bracelet or rings
are.
-But these are adorable.
Forever 21 has the best jewelry.

So go get some for your
Christmas wish list.
Drum roll, please.

-Next up is some makeup products
that we absolutely love.

-We got the Beauty
Blender, which

I use all the time
for my makeup.

It smooths out any clumps
or-- how do you say it?

Globs of makeup that
you have on your face.

And it makes it
look super natural.

But you have to have the
original Beauty Blender,

not any knock offs,
they're not as good.
The original's the best.

And it costs around,
I would say, to $20,
depending on who's selling them.

And they look like
little tear drops,
in case you're wondering.
-They're very soft.
Next up is Bite.

I don't know if
you can see that,
But it says Bite, right there.

And they are like these
lipstick thingies.
They kinda look like crayons.

And you just color
your lips with them.
And this is the--
-It's a bouquet.

This is like a more natural
pink color, which I use.
-More often than I do.
-Brooklyn uses more a red pop.
-Pomegranate.

-But if you guys
are into lipsticks,

or want any lipsticks, Bite
is definitely one of the ones

that you should put on
your Christmas wish list.
We just got if from Sephora.

-My mom's friend
recommended it to us.
And we love if so far.
-They work great.

For Christmas, you can't forget
any of your mint products
from Bath and Body Works.
This is Twisted Peppermint.
We love this smell.

-I think we got
everything in the store--

-Like foam soaps, which I
love foam soaps, by the way.

We got Twisted Mint,
so literally, this

is my favorite object
for Chrismas ever.

And then we got the lotion,
the body bash, the body spray.
There we go.

I lost the thought
there for a minute.

-You don't have to get
the Twisted Peppermint,
but I highly recommend it.

We got other Christmas
flavors, as well.

But they don't even
have to be Christmas.

You can just get
whatever flavor you want.
Flavor?
Is that what you call it?
-Smell.
Scent.
There you go.

-To add to the perfumes
and scenty things,

I have got this neat
perfume from American Eagle.

And my mom got this for
me for back to school.
And I loved it.

They have a couple
of different scents.
This one's Me.
And I absolutely love this one.

-There's Vintage, which
smells very, very good.

-My mom uses that
one all the time.
-Yes.

It's kind of for-- it's kind
of for an older lady smell.

I don't know how you
would say that nicely.
But you know what I mean?
Like, never mind.
-Sophisticated-smelling.
-But it's in my mind.
It makes sense to me.
But anyways.

There's Vintage, and Lip, and
Love, and all the other scents
that you can get.

They usually, the prices
are usually like, $30 to $50

for this perfume, because
they're so amazing.
-They're definitely worth it.

-But they're
definitely worth it.

-We were walking down the
mall, and we saw these.

-It was like a-- it
was like a-- opera.

Slow motion running
towards the window.
(SINGING)

-And then we saw-- and
then we saw Allegiance,
which literally just came out.

Third book to the
Divergent series.

Which you could hear me
talk about the Divergent

series for years, but we finally
found it and convinced our mom

to get is for us for an
early Christmas present,

which really, we've
already read it,
so it doesn't really matter.

And then the other book we found
was The Fault in Our Stars.

And this one is
one that I've heard

really good
recommendations about.

And John Green-- funny
thing about this,

is John Green is
actually YouTuber.

His channel's called
The Blog Brothers.

So if you wanna check
him out, go ahead.
His books are amazing.

And, yeah. if you
guys want these,

don't forget to put these on
your Christmas list as well.
-Next up, our Beats.
Ba bom.
-I love them.
-Ba bom.
-I need them.
-Ba bom
-We wanted them.
But now we have them.

-We saved up our
babysitting money,
and we bought a pair of Beats.
And they are Beat Solos?
Right?
-Beat solos.

-And they come in
all sorts of colors.

-And of course, we
picked the bright green.

-And they're all
foldable and stuff,

so they're easier
to travel with.
-They don't even take up space.

-And we just like pop them
up and then put 'em on.
-Can you hear me?
-No.

-You can hear me, obviously,
if you answered to my question.
They're really good.
-Everything's muffled.
-We use them for editing.
Well hello there.

And we saved up our
money for several months
to by ourselves a pair.
They cost about $200.

But we use them all the time
for editing our videos and such.

If you guys want
some Beats, don't

forget to add that to
your Christmas wish list.
-Mmm.

Half pound Reese's Peanut
Butter Cups from heaven.
-Uh huh.
Uh huh.
-Let's take a moment of silence.

Relish in the beauty of the
peanut butter and chocolate
mix.

-Whoever invented
that was brilliant.
Oh my gosh.
It's like a pie.
-I think I'm gonna cry.
It's so beautiful.
-I know you want it.

So don't forget to put this
on your Christmas list.

-You can find then at
Cracker Barrel for $15.

Next up is something we have
been waiting all year for.

And I know our siblings
have been waiting too,

because we love to play
this game together.
It is Just Dance 2014.

And my family is
obsessed with this game.

We have every
single CD there is.

I have a hysterical story of my
dad playing the kiddie version.

And he had to do Monkeys
Jumping on the Bed.

And he was dancing
like a monkey.
-The whole time.
And it was--
-It was hilarious.

-One of the funniest
moments of my life.

But this game, we have been
waiting all year for it.

And I have this
funny story, again.

In Utah, we had this tradition,
and we would turn this game

on after having a
sleepover with my friends.

We'd sleep over at her
house, and then we'd
eat a bunch of junk food.
And we'd stay up super late.
Then we'd turn this game on.

And we'd have dance competitions
to work off all the calories.

And plus we'd have
fun dancing and doing
competitions and stuff.
-I always won.

-I hope this video
has helped you

guys get some ideas for
your Christmas wish list,

cause I know I was stumped until
I found all this stuff that I
really wanted.

Don't forget to check the link
below for your Just Dance Game,
your own 2014 Just Dance Game.

And be sure to go
to all these stores,

and get all this stuff for your
friends, or you know, whenever.
-If you want to.

-And don't forget
to leave a comment

below on other gifts
you want for Christmas.
And we will see you next week.
-Bye
-See ya.
[MUSIC PLAYING]
-We blink in sync.
It rhymes.
-We blink in sync.
It rhymes.
